GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 962
Short Title: Investing in North Carolina Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Senators Grafstein and Garson (Primary Sponsors).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
May 4, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO APPROPRIATE FUNDS TO RAISE SALARIES FOR TEACHERS, STATE
3 EMPLOYEES, COMMUNITY COLLEGE EMPLOYEES, AND EMPLOYEES OF THE
4 UNIVERSITY OF NORTH CAROLINA AND TO PROVIDE A COST-OF-LIVING
5 INCREASE FOR RETIREES IN THE EVENT THE CURRENT OPERATIONS
6 APPROPRIATIONS ACT DOES NOT BECOME LAW AND TO PROVIDE FOR
7 FUTURE SALARY INCREASES FOR TEACHERS, STATE EMPLOYEES,
8 COMMUNITY COLLEGE EMPLOYEES, AND EMPLOYEES OF THE UNIVERSITY
9 OF NORTH CAROLINA IN THE EVENT FUTURE CURRENT OPERATIONS
10 APPROPRIATIONS ACTS DO NOT BECOME LAW.
11 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
12
13 PART I. CONTINGENT EFFECT FOR CERTAIN PROVISIONS OF THIS ACT
14 SECTION 1. Part II and Part III of this act become effective only if the Current
15 Operations Appropriations Act for the 2026-2027 fiscal year does not become law in the 2025
16 Regular Session of the General Assembly. In that case, the effective date of Part II and Part III
17 of this act shall be the earlier of the following:
18 (1) The first day after the General Assembly adjourns the 2025 Regular Session
19 sine die.
20 (2) January 1, 2027.
21
22 PART II. RAISE TEACHER SALARIES
