36 ALL STATE-SUPPORTED PERSONNEL/FLEXIBLE ADMINISTRATION OF
37 COST-OF-LIVING ADJUSTMENTS
38 SECTION 3.11.(a) The cost-of-living adjustments authorized for the 2026-2027
39 fiscal year shall be paid effective on July 1, 2026, and do not apply to persons separated from
40 service due to resignation, dismissal, reduction in force, death, or retirement or whose last
41 workday is prior to June 30, 2026.
42 SECTION 3.11.(b) The Director of the Budget is granted flexibility to administer
43 the compensation increases enacted by this act.
44 SECTION 3.11.(c) The State employer contribution rates enacted by this act for
45 retirement and related benefits may be deemed by the Director of the Budget for administrative
46 purposes to become effective after July 1 of the applicable fiscal year to provide flexibility in the
47 collection and reconciliation of salary-related contributions as required by law, provided the
48 estimated amount contributed to any affected employee benefit trust equals the amount that
49 would have been contributed to the employee benefit trust if the enacted employer contribution
50 rates had been effective on July 1 of the applicable fiscal year.
